CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, January 28, 1956, pg. 3, reads: "Mamie's Brother - Frank Clark, the brother of Mamie Clark (subject with cap behind white-coated deputy sheriff), enters a sheriff's car behind Earl Williams for a return trip to Western Penitentiary after they testified, reluctantly, that Mamie Clark was not with them and Jack Miller during last year's armed robbery of Stanley Vayson and his daughter of Bellevue. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Sheriff assisting Earl Williams and Frank Clark into dirty Plaza Sheriff's car, Downtown
